* AEG Bo-BoBo-BoWE no. 1565 / NCB No.9, built in 1913 for the Harton Coal Company. Withdrawn in 1988. On display in Marley Hill Yard. Awaiting cosmetic restoration in the future.
* Andrew Barclay Sons &amp; Co. 0-6-0DH no. 615, built in 1977. Operational, on hire to the Aln Valley Railway.
* Armstrong Whitworth no. D22, built in 1933. Operational.
* English Electric and Baguley 2-2wDHR no. 3565, built in 1962. On display.
